   $1 + \frac{2}{3} = \frac{3}{3} + \frac{2}{3} = \frac{5}{3}$

3. Multiply the results of the cube root and the fraction:
   $\sqrt[3]{27} \times \left ( 1+  \frac{2}{3}  \right ) = 3 \times \frac{5}{3}$

   $3 \times \frac{5}{3} = 5$
